      <div type="bibliography" xml:lang="eng">
	<listBibl>
	  <bibl>
	    <ptr target="bibl:Sankalia1969"/>
	  </bibl>
	</listBibl>
      </div>
      <div type="notes" xml:lang="eng">
	<p>This edition is based on <ref target="bibl:Sankalia1969">Sankalia and Gokhale 1969</ref>.</p>
	<p>This is evidently the only Jain record from the Western Deccan of the early centuries CE.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<ab>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  namo arahaṃtānam kātuna<unclear>ṃ</unclear>
	  <lb n="2"/>
	  <unclear>bha</unclear>bhadaṃta <persName key="pers:Pale-Indrarakṣita">idarakhitena</persName> lena<unclear>ṃ</unclear>
	  <lb n="3"/>
	  kārāpita<unclear>ṃ</unclear> poḍhi ca sāh<unclear>ā</unclear> kāhi<lb n="4" break="no"/>saha
	</ab>
      </div>
      <div type="apparatus" xml:lang="eng">
	<appList>
	  <app loc="2">
	    <lem><unclear>bha</unclear></lem>
	    <note resp="bibl:Sankalia1969">The letter seems to have been chipped off at the time of engraving and so the engraver had to incise bha a second time.</note>
	  </app>
	</appList>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
	<p>With reverence to the Arahants,
	   the revered <persName key="pers:Pale-Indrarakṣita">Indrarakṣita</persName>
	   caused this cave to be constructed, as well
	   as a cistern.</p>
      </div>
